04639nam a22006735i 9780520970496DE-B159720240306124542.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240306t20192019cau    fo  d z      eng d  a97805209704967 a10.1525/97805209704962doi  a(DE-B1597)537389  a(OCoLC)1090283111  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  acaucUS-CA 4aKF9632 7aSOC0040002bisacsh04a345.73/0722231 aScott-Hayward, Christine S., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aPunishing Poverty :bHow Bail and Pretrial Detention Fuel Inequalities in the Criminal Justice System /cHenry F. Fradella, Christine S. Scott-Hayward. 1aBerkeley, CA : bUniversity of California Press, c[2019] 4cÂ©2019  a1 online resource (312 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tAcknowledgments -- t1. The Origins and History of Bail in the Common Law Tradition -- t2. Pretrial Release Decisions and Outcomes -- t3. The Problems with Risk-Assessment-Based Bail Determinations -- t4. The Impact of Pretrial Detention -- t5. The Path Forward -- tAppendix -- tNotes -- tReferences -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aMost people in jail have not been convicted of a crime. Instead, they have been accused of a crime and cannot afford to post the bail amount to guarantee their freedom until trial. Punishing Poverty examines how the current system of pretrial release detains hundreds of thousands of defendants awaiting trial. Tracing the historical antecedents of the US bail system, with particular attention to the failures of bail reform efforts in the mid to late twentieth century, the authors describe the painful social and economic impact of contemporary bail decisions. The first book-length treatment to analyze how bail reproduces racial and economic inequality throughout the criminal justice system, Punishing Poverty explores reform efforts, as jurisdictions begin to move away from money bail systems, and the attempts of the bail bond industry to push back against such reforms. This accessibly written book gives a succinct overview of the role of pretrial detention in fueling mass incarceration and is essential reading for researchers and reformers alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArrestzUnited States. 0aBailzUnited States. 0aCriminal justice, Administration ofzUnited States. 0aEqualityzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh1 aFradella, Henry F., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGz978311061013008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCA Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065207908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311066763940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520970496?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520970496423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520970496/original  a978-3-11-061013-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-065207-9  UCA Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-066763-9  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2019  aZDB-23-DSWb2019